<p>Testing <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-transitions/">CSS transitions</a> in Webkit.</p>

<section>
<title><!--<Hypertext Markup Language>-->HTML<!--</>--></title>

<div onmouseover="this.style.opacity = 0" onmouseout="this.style.opacity = 1" style="-webkit-transition: opacity 1s linear; background-color: #DDD; border: 5px solid black;"><p>This div will fade out when hovered over. In browsers that do not support this animation, there will be graceful degradation, as the div will simply fade out immediately.</p>
<code><![CDATA[<div onmouseover="this.style.opacity = 0" onmouseout="this.style.opacity = 1" style="-webkit-transition: opacity 1s linear; background-color: #DDD; border: 5px solid black;"/>]]></code>
</div> 

<div style="text-align: center; margin: 1em auto; background-color: skyblue; border: 5px solid #DDD; -webkit-transition: -webkit-transform 3s ease-in" onmousedown="this.style.webkitTransform = 'rotate(+360deg)'" onmouseup="this.style.webkitTransform = 'rotate(0deg)'">
<p>This div will do a spin the first time it is clicked!</p>
<code><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center; margin: 1em auto; background-color: skyblue; border: 5px solid #DDD; -webkit-transition: -webkit-transform 3s ease-in" onmousedown="this.style.webkitTransform = 'rotate(+360deg)'" onmouseup="this.style.webkitTransform = 'rotate(0deg)'"/>]]></code>
</div>

<div style="text-align: center; background-color: maroon; color: white; -webkit-transition: all 500ms linear; border: 10px solid black;" onmouseover="this.style.border = '20px solid blue'" onmouseout="this.style.border = '10px solid black'"> 
<p>Borders can also be animated. This box has a simple border animation where the border will both grow in thickness and change color when the box is hovered.</p>
<code><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center; background-color: maroon; color: white; -webkit-transition: all 500ms linear; border: 10px solid black;" onmouseover="this.style.border = '20px solid blue'" onmouseout="this.style.border = '10px solid black'"/>]]></code>
</div>

